cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

This paper discusses a method for reducing the memory and computational footprint of deep neural networks, which is a common problem in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The method proposed in the paper involves a solver that combines gradient descent and k-means, which are commonly used in optimization and clustering algorithms, respectively, suggesting that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) may also be relevant sub-categories.
